      "instruction": "<p>Combine the<strong> tomato paste</strong> with the <strong>remaining rice vinegar</strong>, <strong>chilli flakes </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!), <strong>tamari soy sauce</strong>, <strong>ketchup</strong>, <strong>cornflour</strong>,<strong> </strong>and<strong> </strong>1 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tbsp]</span> <strong>sugar </strong>in a small bowl</p><p>Add 100ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[200ml] </span><strong>cold water </strong>and mix it all together –<strong> </strong>this is your<strong> chilli sauce mix</strong></p><p>Once the tomato has softened, add the<strong> chilli sauce mix</strong> to the pan and cook for 2-3 min or until thickened</p>",
